<%- include('partials/head', { title: 'pricing' }) %>
<%- include('partials/nav') %>

<div class="page" id="main-content" role="main">
<section class="page-section">
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="page-header a-fade-up">
      <div class="section-tag">pricing</div>
      <h2>three tiers. one job. no kickbacks.</h2>
      <p>free to start, cheap to stay, premium if you need the firehose. all plans include extraction, verdicts, and the weekly digest. no hidden fees, no per-item charges, no data selling.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="pricing-toggle a-fade-up">
      <button class="pt-btn pt-btn-active" data-period="month">monthly</button>
      <button class="pt-btn" data-period="year">annual <span class="pt-save">save ~20–30%</span></button>
    </div>
    <div class="pricing-grid pricing-grid-3 a-fade-up pricing-a" id="pricingGrid">

      <!-- Free Tier -->
      <div class="price-card" data-month="0" data-year="0">
        <div class="price-badge">free</div>
        <h3>starter</h3>
        <div class="for">for trying perch. out — no card needed</div>
        <div class="price-amount"><span class="pa-val">£0</span><span class="pa-period"></span></div>
        <div class="price-alt"><span class="pa-alt"></span></div>
        <div style="font-size:11px;color:var(--accent);margin-bottom:12px;font-weight:500;">no payment needed. ever.</div>
        <ul>
          <li>up to 5 renewals tracked</li>
          <li>email &amp; document extraction</li>
          <li>weekly digest (read only)</li>
          <li>renew / cancel / renegotiate verdicts</li>
          <li>1 forwarding inbox</li>
          <li>no ads, no data selling</li>
        </ul>
        <a href="/waitlist" class="btn-secondary">get early access →</a>
      </div>

      <!-- Standard Tier -->
      <div class="price-card featured" data-month="8.99" data-year="89">
        <div class="price-badge">popular</div>
        <h3>standard</h3>
        <div class="for">for personal and family use</div>
        <div class="price-amount"><span class="pa-val">£8.99</span><span class="pa-period">/month</span></div>
        <div class="price-alt"><span class="pa-alt"></span></div>
        <div style="font-size:11px;color:var(--accent);margin-bottom:12px;font-weight:500;">free during early access — no payment needed</div>
        <ul>
          <li>unlimited renewals tracked</li>
          <li>email &amp; document extraction</li>
          <li>full weekly digest</li>
          <li>renew / cancel / renegotiate verdicts</li>
          <li>price history tracking</li>
          <li>savings dashboard</li>
          <li>calendar view of all renewals</li>
          <li>1 forwarding inbox</li>
        </ul>
        <a href="/waitlist" class="btn-secondary">get early access →</a>
      </div>

      <!-- Premium Tier -->
      <div class="price-card" data-month="19.99" data-year="199">
        <div class="price-badge">premium</div>
        <h3>premium</h3>
        <div class="for">for micro-businesses and power users</div>
        <div class="price-amount"><span class="pa-val">£19.99</span><span class="pa-period">/month</span></div>
        <div class="price-alt"><span class="pa-alt"></span></div>
        <div style="font-size:11px;color:var(--accent);margin-bottom:12px;font-weight:500;">free during early access — no payment needed</div>
        <ul>
          <li>everything in standard</li>
          <li>3 forwarding inboxes</li>
          <li>vendor &amp; saas contract tracking</li>
          <li>team digest forwarding</li>
          <li>market benchmarking</li>
          <li>csv / pdf export</li>
          <li>priority support</li>
        </ul>
        <a href="/waitlist" class="btn-secondary">get early access →</a>
      </div>

    </div>
    <p class="price-footnote">no surprises. cancel any time. annual billing saves ~20–30% depending on tier.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="page-section faq-section">
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="page-header a-fade-up">
      <div class="section-tag">questions</div>
      <h2>questions we get asked.</h2>
      <p>we've been asking people what would stop them signing up. here's what came back, and here's how we answer.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="a-fade-up" style="max-width:720px;">
      <div class="faq-item">
        <div class="faq-q">what's the catch with the free tier?<span class="icon">+</span></div>
        <div class="faq-a">no catch. you get extraction, verdicts, and the weekly digest for up to 5 items. no ads, no data selling — the same privacy we give every tier. if you never hit the limit, you never need to pay. that said, most people have more than 5 renewals, and once you see what you're missing, the standard tier pays for itself.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <div class="faq-q">how is this different from a budgeting app?<span class="icon">+</span></div>
        <div class="faq-a">budgeting apps categorise past spending. they tell you what you already spent. perch. looks forward — it tells you what's about to renew and whether you should act. entirely different time horizon, entirely different job.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <div class="faq-q">do you auto-cancel things on my behalf?<span class="icon">+</span></div>
        <div class="faq-a">never. you always make the call. we surface the deadline and the recommended action, but we never touch an account, cancel a policy, or send anything on your behalf. that's not a limitation — it's the point.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <div class="faq-q">what happens to the emails and documents i send you?<span class="icon">+</span></div>
        <div class="faq-a">we extract the renewal details immediately and store nothing beyond what's needed to track your items. no training models on your data. no sharing with third parties. you can delete any item at any time.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <div class="faq-q">what if i don't get renewal emails?<span class="icon">+</span></div>
        <div class="faq-a">that happens more often than you'd think. if you don't have the email, you can upload a pdf statement, a screenshot, or even a photo of a letter. we'll extract the same details from whatever you give us.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <div class="faq-q">what do the verdicts actually say?<span class="icon">+</span></div>
        <div class="faq-a">we label each item renew, cancel, or renegotiate based on price changes, usage, and market context. renegotiate means the price went up and you have leverage. cancel means you're paying for something you're not using. renew means everything looks fine — no action needed.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <div class="faq-q">can i try it before paying?<span class="icon">+</span></div>
        <div class="faq-a">the free tier is free forever — no trial, no card, no expiry. if you need more than 5 items, the standard and premium tiers are also free during early access. we'll give plenty of notice before billing starts, and you can leave at any time.</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
</div>

<script>
document.querySelectorAll('.pt-btn').forEach(function(btn) {
  btn.addEventListener('click', function() {
    document.querySelectorAll('.pt-btn').forEach(function(b) { b.classList.remove('pt-btn-active'); });
    btn.classList.add('pt-btn-active');
    var period = btn.getAttribute('data-period');
    document.querySelectorAll('.price-card').forEach(function(card) {
      var month = parseFloat(card.getAttribute('data-month'));
      var year = parseFloat(card.getAttribute('data-year'));
      var valEl = card.querySelector('.pa-val');
      var periodEl = card.querySelector('.pa-period');
      var altEl = card.querySelector('.pa-alt');
      if (period === 'month') {
        valEl.textContent = month === 0 ? '£0' : '\u00A3' + month.toFixed(2);
        periodEl.textContent = month === 0 ? '' : '/month';
        altEl.textContent = year === 0 ? '' : 'or \u00A3' + year + '/year (save ~' + Math.round((1 - year/(month*12)) * 100) + '%)';
      } else {
        valEl.textContent = year === 0 ? '£0' : '\u00A3' + year;
        periodEl.textContent = year === 0 ? '' : '/year';
        var equiv = month > 0 ? (year / 12).toFixed(2) : '0';
        altEl.textContent = year === 0 ? '' : '\u00A3' + equiv + '/month equivalent';
      }
    });
  });
});
</script>
<%- include('partials/footer') %>